properties.label: Account ID
properties.name: accountId
properties.hint: Required for creating a new case.  Salesforce Account ID to use for case.

properties.label: Case ID
properties.name: caseId
properties.hint: If a Case ID is specified, the case will be updated.  If no Case ID is specified, a new case will be created.

properties.label: Case Type
properties.name: caseType
properties.hint: Required for creating a new case.  Accepted  values are "Standard Case", "Managed Services", or "Internal Case"

properties.label: Case Origin
properties.name: caseOrigin
properties.hint: Required for creating a new case.  Salesforce does limit the values that can be provided here.  When creating a Managed Services case, you should use the value 'ARC' as the caseOrigin.  You can contact IT to get the full list of supported values.

properties.label: Contact ID
properties.name: contactId
properties.hint: Salesforce Contact to be used as the contact on the case (this contact will be sent case notifications).

properties.label: Description
properties.name: description
properties.hint: Required for creating a new case.  Description line for the case.

properties.label: Ipims org ID
properties.name: ipimsOrgId
properties.hint: Instead of specifying the Salesforce Account ID, you can optionally specify the IPIMS Platform Org ID.  A matching Salesforce Account will be searched for by navigating from Platform Org -> Platform Customer -> Salesforce Account.

properties.label: Issue Type
properties.name: issueType
properties.hint: Specifies the type of case. There are many different values that are available, contact IT for all the options.  For "Managed Services" cases, you would most likely use "Outbound RFI" or "Inbound RFI".

properties.label: Private comment
properties.name: privateComment
properties.hint: If specified, this private comment will be added to the case.

properties.label: Product
properties.name: product
properties.hint: Product associated with this case.  Salesforce does have a restricted list to use for these values, please contact IT to get a full list of available options.

properties.label: Severity
properties.name: severity
properties.hint: Accepted  values are "1 - Mission Critical", "2 - High", or "3 - Medium"

properties.label: Status
properties.name: status
properties.hint: Status for the case.  Accepted value is "Closed".  This field should only be used to close a case (otherwise should be left undefined or blank).

properties.label: Subject
properties.name: subject
properties.hint: Required for creating a new case.  Subject line for the case.

properties.label: Time Zone to Receive Support
properties.name: timezone
properties.hint: Accepted values are "(GMT+10:00) Australian Eastern Standard Time (Australia/Brisbane)", "(GMT+08:00) Singapore Standard Time (Asia/Singapore)", "(GMT+01:00) British Summer Time (Europe/London)", "(GMT-04:00) Eastern Daylight Time (America/New_York)", "(GMT-05:00) Central Daylight Time (America/Mexico_City)", "(GMT-07:00) Pacific Daylight Time (America/Los_Angeles)"
